he can't hear us.

11:19.054 --> 11:21.348
I love names.
I'm kind of a name guy.

11:21.389 --> 11:23.683
You know, the right one
can send a shudder

11:23.725 --> 11:24.851
down your spine.

11:24.893 --> 11:26.895
Wanna know
what I go by?

11:26.936 --> 11:28.730
- There's not a person
on the West Coast

11:28.772 --> 11:31.399
that hasn't heard
of Sweet Tooth.

11:31.441 --> 11:32.567
- See what I mean?

11:32.609 --> 11:36.154
I mean, you really
feel that in your bones!

11:36.196 --> 11:38.531
What's your name,
friend?

11:38.573 --> 11:40.950
- John Doe.

11:40.992 --> 11:42.744
- Nah, I'll give it
a seven.

11:42.786 --> 11:44.120
- Hey, I didn't
pick it.

11:44.162 --> 11:45.789
I don't know what name
I was born with

11:45.830 --> 11:49.167
or who I am really.

11:49.209 --> 11:51.753
- Oh, amnesia.
What's your brand?

11:51.795 --> 11:54.714
Post-traumatic,
transient, dissociative?

11:54.756 --> 11:55.799
- All I know
is my first memory

11:55.840 --> 11:57.801
is me waking up
in my car

11:57.842 --> 11:59.302
with blood coming
out of my head.

11:59.344 --> 12:00.887
- Wait, that's
my first memory too!

12:00.929 --> 12:03.139
My head
covered in blood.

12:03.181 --> 12:04.307
Of course,
it was being pushed

12:04.349 --> 12:05.725
out of my mom's
whisker biscuit, but...

12:05.767 --> 12:06.893
- Whoa!
You remember that?

12:06.935 --> 12:10.397
- Oh, yeah.
I remember everything.

12:10.438 --> 12:12.190
You should consider
yourself lucky.

12:12.232 --> 12:14.734
There are some things
I wish I could forget.

12:14.776 --> 12:17.529
Like the time
I shit my pants

12:17.570 --> 12:20.490
in my elementary school
production of "Oklahoma".

12:20.532 --> 12:24.160
I can still see
the audience's faces

12:24.202 --> 12:26.705
laughing,
mocking.

12:29.416 --> 12:31.501
Did you know Sisqo's
real name was Mark?

12:37.924 --> 12:39.718
[grunting]

12:41.011 --> 12:42.637
- [Stu] Oh, a rock.

12:44.973 --> 12:46.516
- Man, what is
wrong with you?

12:46.558 --> 12:48.601
You holding in a fart
or something?

12:48.643 --> 12:51.271
- If the truck is so important,
why don't they just move it?

12:51.312 --> 12:53.440
Something doesn't
smell right, man.

12:53.481 --> 12:55.608
- Smells good to me.

12:55.650 --> 12:57.569
Back in Seattle,
they treated us like morons.

12:57.610 --> 13:00.405
Now look at us;
we holding .30-cals, dude!

13:00.447 --> 13:03.033
